    <h2>Hit rates and race</h2>
    <p>One way is to move past the act of stopping a driver and to think about the steps that follow. Once a driver is stopped, the police then make a decision to search the individual, or not. This search may then be successful â€” or not. The hit rate is the number of successful searches of a given demographic divided by the number of people of that demographic that were searched. In an ideal world, hit rates would be the same across races. </p>
        <p>The rate of success in finding contraband is lower among minorities than white people. This suggests that more minorities are searched based on flimsier evidence once they're stopped when compared to white people.</p>
